			<title>[ January 14, 2024] CFP for conference or similar: Toronto Philosophy of Religion Workshop on God and Value Theory</title>
			<link>https://philevents.org/event/show/118005</link>
						<description><p>The Toronto Working Group in Philosophy of Religion will hold a workshop on the topic God and Value Theory (broadly construed) on June 11-13, 2024 in Toronto, Ontario. </p>
<p>The workshop will be read-ahead: accepted authors should expect to have a conference paper ready for distribution by May 1, 2024, and should come to the workshop ready to discuss all papers. </p>
<p>Keynote sessions will be given by Mark Murphy, Leigh Vicens, and Scott Davison. </p>
<p>The workshop will feature both invited and submitted papers. Those interested in giving a submitted paper should prepare an abstract of 300-500 words for blind review and submit it here:<a10px href="https://forms.gle/16Hy63VeR8uo7MDf6">https://forms.gle/16Hy63VeR8uo7MDf6</a10px></p>
<p>Possible topics include but are not limited to:</p>
<p>- divine goodness</p>
<p>- the relationship between theism and aesthetics</p>
<p>- the role of religion in public life</p>
<p>- the cardinal virtues as they relate to theism</p>
<p>- the axiology of theism</p>
<p>- theism and epistemic value</p>
<p>- the problem of evil</p>
<p>Work on any of these questions situated in particular theistic traditions is most welcome.</p>
<p>The deadline for submission is 11:59:59 EST on 14 January 2024. Those with questions about the workshop should contact one of the co-organizers: Liz Jackson (lizjackson111@torontomu.ca), Klaas Kraay (kraay@torontomu.ca), and Daniel Rubio (danielkfrubio@gmail.com).</p></description>
